      "full_name": "Kuzyakin Dmitry Vasilevich",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "Dmitry Kuzyakin is the founder, General Director and co-owner of LLC “Center for Integrated Unmanned Solutions”, a company that is part of the Russian military and industrial complex. LLC “Center for Integrated Unmanned Solutions” deals with the full cycle of first-person view (FPV) systems for combat use, from training personnel in piloting and effective use to production of end devices and ground equipment. Based in Zhukovsky in the Moscow Oblast, which is the centre of Russian aviation research, LLC “Center for Integrated Unmanned Solutions” develops and produces unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) which are provided to the Russian Armed Forces and used in Russia’s war of aggression against Ukraine.",
